I did my test swatches and most of the colors are a close match to what they show. A few are way off, but still pretty colors. All of my swatches are two coats. The only issue I had was with the black, which isn't shown in my photos. Even after at least 5 minutes, I couldn't get the color to cure. The bottles seem to be pretty full and none are goopy or thick. Although there are quite a few reds and pinks, it's still a good selection, especially for the price.
Good set of gel polishes at a great price!

This is a nice set of gel polishes. Some of the colors aren't close to the colors in the sellers photos, but they are still nice. The opaque colors looked pretty good with just one coat, but I used two coats. The glitter swatches have two coats on as well. The matte top coat has a very strong smell, but seems to work really well. The regular top coat cures to a shiny finish and seems good too. All of the layers cured in two minutes each with my lamp.
Nice set of reds/pinks. Good coverage.

profile:
**User Profile Summary:**

- **Product Preference:** Enjoys a wide range of nail polish colors, maintaining a strong inclination towards vibrant shades like red and burgundy, while also exploring pastels and glittery finishes.
- **Formulation Insight:** Favors gel nail products with both glossy and matte finishes, indicating a willingness to try varied aesthetic options.
- **Quality Expectations:** Expects accurate color representations and good coverage, often achieving satisfactory results with fewer coats. However, has experienced inconsistencies in product volume, particularly with packaging.
- **Experience Level:** Intermediate user who is skilled at performing swatches and evaluating application outcomes, comfortable using layering techniques.
- **Price Sensitivity:** Values affordability and expects good value for money, particularly noting that packaging quality and product quantity should align with pricing.
- **Curing Performance:** Anticipates effective curing times, finding success with typical two-minute cures for base, color, and top coats.
- **Visual Appeal:** Prioritizes aesthetic qualities in nail products and enjoys experimenting with diverse designs and finishes, including glitter.

Overall, the user seeks well-priced products that offer a broad color selection, reliable performance in application and curing, and visual versatility, while expressing some concern over product quantity relative to cost.
